                <div class="col-75">
                    <P>Side effects of paracetamol are usually mild, though haematological reactions including thrombocytopenia, leukopenia, pancytopenia, neutropenia, and agranulocytosis have been reported. Pancreatitis, skin rashes, and other allergic reactions occur occasionally.</P>
                  </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tab-pane fade" id="des-seven" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="precaution-warning">
                <div class="col-75">
                   <P>Paracetamol and Caffeine should be given cautiously in the following cases: In patients with hepatic or renal failure, in patients taking other hepatotoxic medication. Prolonged use of the drug without consulting a physician should be avoided.</P>
                  </div>
            </div>

